The paper focuses on advancing our understanding of software vulnerabilities, automating their identification, and analyzing their impact, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also deals with the curation of a dataset of vulnerabilities and their fixes, which is relevant to the computer security (cs.CR) category. The use of machine learning classifiers to automatically identify security-relevant commits in code repositories suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper's emphasis on making the dataset a shared effort involving open-source communities, academia, and the industry aligns with the social and information sciences (cs.SI) category.
